<paragraph blockId="16.[824,1320,937,997]" pageId="16" pageNumber="43">
<heading bold="true" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="16" pageNumber="43" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="43">
Key to the subspecies of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Homalium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="planiflorum">Homalium planiflorum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<keyStep pageId="16" pageNumber="43">
<paragraph blockId="16.[824,1475,1015,1295]" pageId="16" pageNumber="43">
<keyLead pageId="16" pageNumber="43">
1. Inflorescences usually racemose (rarely a racemiform or few-branched panicle), usually borne along much of the length of small twigs; flowers whitish to pale green, pale yellow, or cream-colored; widely distributed ..................... ....................................................... 9a. 
<taxonomicName box="[1278,1474,1142,1167]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Homalium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="planiflorum" subSpecies="planiflorum">
