<emphasis bold="true" box="[1348,1474,1142,1166]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="43">planiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[824,1475,1015,1295]" pageId="16" pageNumber="43">
<keyLead pageId="16" pageNumber="43">
1a. Inflorescences racemose, usually clustered near twig ends, or paniculate with few long racemoid branches; flowers pink to reddish; confined to southeastern Madagascar ..... ........................................................9b. 
<taxonomicName box="[1284,1474,1270,1295]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Homalium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="planiflorum" subSpecies="roseiflorum">
subsp. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1355,1474,1270,1294]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="43">roseiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
